            <div type="edition">
            <ab>
                <lb n="1"/> <persName><supplied reason="lost"><name type="praenomen" key="Marcus"><expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arci</ex></expan></name></supplied> <name type="gentilicium" key="Perperna"><supplied reason="lost">P</supplied>erpernae</name></persName> <persName><name type="praenomen" key="Marcus"><expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arci</ex></expan></name></persName> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>iberti</ex></expan> <unclear cert="low">N</unclear> <gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/>
                <lb n="2"/> ossa hic sita su<supplied reason="lost">nt</supplied>.
                <lb n="3"/> <persName><supplied reason="lost"><name type="praenomen" key="Marcus"><expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arcus</ex></expan></name></supplied> <name type="gentilicium" key="Perperna"><supplied reason="lost">P</supplied>erperna</name> <persName><name type="praenomen" key="Marcus"><expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arci</ex></expan></name></persName> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>ibertus</ex></expan> <name type="cognomen">Phila<unclear>d</unclear><gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/></name></persName>
                <lb n="4"/> politor eborariu<supplied reason="lost">s</supplied>.
            </ab></div>
            
            <div type="translation">
                <p>The bones of Marcus Perperna, freedman of Marcus, are situated here. Marcus Perperna Phila[   ], polisher of and worker in ivory, (dedicated this).</p></div>

            <div type="commentary">
            <p>Line 1 breaks off with an unclear letter, with a vertical stroke on the left being all that is preserved; an "N" is supposed here which presumably began the individual's cognomen. While the Penn Museum treats "politor eborariu[s]" as a single vocational epithet, namely "ivory polisher," given the attestation of "eborarius" being used independently elsewhere (in Justinian's codex, for instance) to refer to a class of ivory workers, "politor" and "eborarius" have here been treated as two distinct epithets.</p></div>

